FT  09 MAY 94 / Italy wins sugar refinery deal
Savola Company of Saudi Arabia said yesterday it had awarded Italy's TPL
(Tecnologie Progetti Lavori Spa) a contract to build a sugar refinery worth
Dollars 173m (Pounds 118.4m), Reuter reports from Manama.
The refinery, which will be the biggest in the Middle East, will be built in
Jeddah port on the Red Sea.
It will have an annual capacity of 500,000 tonnes of sugar and 20,000 tonnes
of molasses. In earlier statements Savola has estimated the refinery would
cost around SR650m (Pounds 114.3m). Two Italian companies - TPL and
Technimont Gruppo Ferruzzi - and Taylor Woodrow of the UK had competed for
the contract.
